Description: LACBC is a membership-based nonprofit organization that works to make all communities in L.A. County healthy, safe.
Headquarters Regions: Greater Los Angeles Area, West Coast, Western US
Full Description: The Los Angeles County Bicycle Coalition (LACBC) is a membership-based nonprofit organization that works to make all communities in L.A. County healthy, safe, and fun places to ride a bike through advocacy, education, and outreach. Founded in 1998 by bicycle advocates Joe Linton and Ron Milam, LACBC brings together the diverse bicycling community in a united mission to improve the bicycling environment and quality of life for the entire region. Despite Los Angeles’ reputation as a car-centric region, LACBC has emerged as one of the most innovative and wide-reaching bicycle advocacy nonprofits in the country. LACBC has played a major role in the growing cycling movement here in L.A. Our vision is to improve the built environment in Los Angeles, so that all cyclists—low-income, commuter, recreational, families, and women—can safely navigate L.A. County streets. Through the help of our strong volunteer network, LACBC accomplishes this vision in our campaigns to increase bicycle infrastructure throughout the 88 cities in the county. The Los Angeles County Bicycle Coalition builds a better, more bike-able Los Angeles by bringing diverse communities together to improve the bicycling environment and quality of life for the whole county.

Organization Name: The University of California Transportation Center(UCTC)
Description: The University of California Transportation Center is a multi-campus organization headquartered on the UC Berkeley campus.
Headquarters Regions: San Francisco Bay Area, West Coast, Western US
Full Description: The University of California Transportation Center (UCTC) is a multi-campus organization headquartered on the UC Berkeley campus. It carries out basic and applied research in three related areas: environmental sustainability, economic competitiveness, and livability. Its research findings are disseminated in multiple ways, including journal publications, seminars, webinars, and conference proceedings as well as less technical forums aimed at reaching wider audiences. It also operates with an educational mission, supporting students through graduate research appointments, dissertation help grants, curriculum development, new graduate course sponsorship, and an annual UCTC Student Conference. Under SAFETEA-LU, UCTC researchers have advanced knowledge and shaped practice in areas such as urban logistics, transportation and land-use modeling and integration, congestion pricing, eco-driving, clean-vehicle technologies, inter-vehicle communications, transit performance evaluations, lifecycle costing of transport infrastructure, transit-oriented development, environmental justice, parking policy, dynamic traffic operations, freight competition, and air quality impacts of transportation improvements. The center provides approximately $2 million per year for faculty research, dissertation awards, scholarships and fellowships. At Irvine, the center has supported nearly 100 faculty research and dissertation projects, and provided approximately $600,000 for undergraduate scholarships and graduate fellowships in transportation engineering and transportation economics. The University of California Transportation Center was established by congressional mandate in 1988.

Full Description: Web Crons, Uptime Alerts, Performance Reports. Choose the URL of your script and choose a frequency to run. (i.e, every minute, hour, etc).  Basic Web Crons: - Choose the URL of your script and choose a frequency to run. (i.e, every minute, hour, etc) Advanced Web Crons: - GET, PUT, POST, DELETE + custom data payload - Basic authentication via username / password - Output parsing (must contain, must not contain) or Regular Expression - Custom Ports - Follow-up alerts. Re-send alerts based on custom rules Uptime Alerts: - Receive alerts the moment a script fails. Choose to send alerts immediatly or after a certain number of consecutive failures. Alerts are sent up to 3 ways simutaneously: Email Alerts: - Email alerts contain detailed information about why a cron failed. SMS (Text Message) Alerts: - SMS alerts contain a brief description of a failure with a link to see details about the error. Phone (Voice) Alerts: - Receive an automated phone call with details about the error message. The call with explain which cron failed with a brief explanation. Performance Reports: - Automatically track performance metrics related to your web cron. Response Time: - Track the response time of every script. Choose filter by Average, Max, Min Uptime History: - Track the history of all uptime and downtime events. Keeps running totals of uptime over the past Day, Week and Month. Real Time Updates: - No need to refresh to see and updated status. Perfect for dashboards.
